// Datasheet for the `net` device — its exposed TYPE (a device's types live in its datasheet, not its
// impl). `socket` is a primitive opaque handle for a TCP socket (a raw fd in the opaque cell). You
// may move/borrow/return a `socket` but not write a raw value into it; the operations in net.arche
// are the only way to act on it. No storage requirements.
socket :: opaque;
